definitions.definition: A balsamic resin from the bark of Styrax trees used in perfumes, incense, and medicine; benzoin resin .
A type of tree which produces benzoin or has similar properties; specifically, Styrax benzoin , Lindera benzoin ; a Benjamin bush .

main_definition: A balsamic resin from the bark of Styrax trees used in perfumes, incense, and medicine; benzoin resin .
